        <abstract> 
<p>Discusses heterostyly in <hi rend="italic">Hottonia</hi>.</p>  
<p>Criticises L. C. Treviranus’ statements on <hi rend="italic">Primula longiflora</hi>’s having short-styled form.</p>  
<p>Describes his results with crossing different coloured primroses. Will let CD, when he reads his paper, decide whether his finding white and red varieties perfectly sterile when crossed, yet fertile <hi rend="italic">inter se</hi>, ought to be published.</p>  
<p>Difficulty in getting his orchid paper published in <hi rend="italic">Edinburgh New Philosophical Journal</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
